Concurrency (in Go) : Concurrency means the ability of a program to run multiple tasks at the same time independently.
in short - The ability of a program to execute multiple tasks at the same time.

Garbage Collection (in Go) : Garbage Collection (GC) is an automatic memory management process where the system automatically frees memory that is no longer being used by the program.
in short - An automatic memory management system that removes unused objects from memory.

